article.headline: Indiana St. 80, Bradley 66
article.story: TERRE HAUTE, Ind. -- Aaron Carter scored 19 points and Dwayne Lathan added 18 as Indiana State defeated Bradley 80-66 Wednesday night. Steve McWhorter and RJ Mahurin each had 10 points for the Sycamores (6-6, 1-0 Missouri Valley), who have won nine straight at home. Andrew Warren led the Braves (6-6, 0-1) with 20 points, Will Egolf had 14 and Dyricus Simms-Edwards 13. Indiana State scored 15 points off 17 Bradley turnovers, never trailed and led by as much as 19. Carter was 7 of 12 from the field with three 3-pointers for the Sycamores, who were up 39-22 at halftime.
